PRETORIA, South Africa, March 5, 2021/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The cumulative number of COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 1,517,666. Regrettably, 96 more COVID-19 related deaths have been reported. This brings the total to 50,462 deaths. Our recoveries now stand at 1,436,010, representing a recovery rate of 94,6%.